  "text": "The DOM event dispatch path in Firefox flows through these key files: (1) **Event creation**: `EventDispatcher::CreateEvent` in EventDispatcher.cpp creates DOM Event objects from WidgetEvents based on event class (mouse, keyboard, etc.), and `Event::ConstructorInit` in Event.cpp initializes them. (2) **Event target identification & chain building**: `EventDispatcher::Dispatch` in EventDispatcher.cpp builds the event target chain by calling `EventTargetChainItem::GetEventTargetParent` on each target, walking up from the target to the root via `mParentTarget`. EventTarget.cpp provides the `DispatchEvent` entry point from JS. (3) **Capture/bubble phase traversal**: `EventTargetChainItem::HandleEventTargetChain` in EventDispatcher.cpp iterates the chain in reverse for capture (lines 517-585), then handles the target phase (lines 587-611), then forward for bubble (lines 613-648), and finally re-dispatches for the system event group (lines 651-687). (4) **Event listener invocation**: `EventTargetChainItem::HandleEvent` calls `EventListenerManager::HandleEvent` (in EventListenerManager.h/.cpp), which delegates to `HandleEventInternal` to iterate registered listeners, and `HandleEventSingleListener` to invoke each individual listener callback via WebIDL or XPCOM. (5) **Default action execution**: `EventStateManager::PostHandleEvent` in EventStateManager.cpp handles platform default behaviors (mouse, keyboard, focus, etc.), and `nsPresShellEventCB::HandleEvent` in PresShell.cpp provides the callback between default and system group dispatch to handle frame-level events. PresShell.cpp also contains `DispatchEventToDOM` which determines the event target from the frame tree.",
